Class AbstractCFG<I, T extends IBasicBlock<I>>

java.lang.Object
com.ibm.wala.cfg.AbstractCFG<I,T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
ControlFlowGraph<I,T>, MinimalCFG<T>, Constants, EdgeManager<T>, Graph<T>, NodeManager<T>, NumberedEdgeManager<T>, NumberedGraph<T>, NumberedNodeManager<T>, Iterable<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
AstTranslator.AstCFG, DexCFG, InducedCFG, ShrikeCFG
public abstract class AbstractCFG<I, T extends IBasicBlock<I>> extends Object implements ControlFlowGraph<I,T>, MinimalCFG<T>, Constants
Common functionality for ControlFlowGraph implementations.

    • getExceptionalSuccessors

      public List<T> getExceptionalSuccessors(T b)
      Description copied from interface: MinimalCFG
      The order of blocks returned must indicate the exception-handling scope. So the first block is the first candidate catch block, and so on. With this invariant one can compute the exceptional control flow for a given exception type.
      Specified by:
      getExceptionalSuccessors in interface MinimalCFG<I>
      Returns:
      the basic blocks which may be reached from b via exceptional control flow
